    <tags>mcp claude reasoning ai anthropic ml llm</tags>
    <summary>MCP server providing 15 structured reasoning tools for Claude Code and Claude Desktop</summary>
    <description>
MCP Reasoning Server - A high-performance MCP server that provides structured reasoning capabilities for Claude Code and Claude Desktop. Built in Rust with 15 reasoning modes including:

- Core reasoning: linear, tree, divergent, reflection, checkpoint, auto
- Graph-of-Thoughts: Complex reasoning chain building
- Analysis tools: Bias/fallacy detection, decision analysis, evidence evaluation
- Advanced: Timeline reasoning, Monte Carlo Tree Search, counterfactual analysis
- Infrastructure: Pre-configured workflows, usage metrics

Features:
- Session persistence with SQLite
- Self-improvement system with circuit breaker safety
- Extended thinking budgets for complex reasoning
- Streaming API with progress notifications
- 2,020 tests with 95%+ coverage
- Zero unsafe code, production-ready

Perfect for developers working with Claude on complex reasoning tasks including code review, debugging, architecture decisions, and strategic planning.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/quanticsoul4772/mcp-reasoning/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md</releaseNotes>
    <dependencies>
      <!-- No runtime dependencies - statically linked binary -->
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
